&lt;li class=&quot;font-claude-response-body whitespace-normal break-words pl-2&quot;&gt;Own the AI-powered support and self

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Help make the world more hospitable &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The hospitality industry is uniquely human, and it deserves technology that’s just as inspiring as the people behind it. At Mews, we’re transforming the industry with a platform that helps hotels run smarter, move faster and create better guest experiences.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll work with smart, curious people who care deeply about what they do. You’ll have autonomy and the trust to make good decisions and move quickly. And you’ll enjoy a real sense of purpose as you see the impact of what we’re building.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you’re motivated by ownership, curiosity and meaningful impact, and are driven to deliver consistent high performance, you’ll feel at home here.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Let&#39;s get into the specifics. It’s impossible to capture every nuance of a role – especially at a rapidly growing company like Mews – but if we had to distil it into a job description (which we do because this is a job description), it would be this:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p data-renderer-start-pos=&quot;20&quot; data-local-id=&quot;3eea080864d4&quot;&gt;Long Stays are one of the fastest-growing segments in hospitality. The guests are different, the economics are different, the operational model is different – and the software most hotels use to run them was built for none of it. This role exists to change that.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-renderer-start-pos=&quot;284&quot; data-local-id=&quot;0d8a790432ae&quot;&gt;As Director of Product and Engineering, Long Stays, you will own this segment end-to-end: the strategy, the product, the technical direction and the outcomes. You will lead a small team of product builders while building yourself – writing specs, making product calls, contributing directly to what ships. Reporting to the VP of Product and Engineering, you are the single accountable owner for Long Stays as a product capability within Mews.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-renderer-start-pos=&quot;728&quot; data-local-id=&quot;8f8f59dc31d8&quot;&gt;This is not a role for someone who wants to manage at arm&#39;s length. The team is lean by design. The expectation is that you are in the work – discovering problems, setting direction, reviewing code and copy, shipping things. You will use AI agents and internal tooling to extend what the team can do, and you will raise the ceiling on what that looks like as you go.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-renderer-start-pos=&quot;1096&quot; data-local-id=&quot;77b83b6eca70&quot;&gt;Your success will be measured against a blend of commercial and product metrics – ARR growth, embedded payments revenue, and product north star metrics we will define together. You own both the quality of what ships and the outcomes it drives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p id=&quot;What-you-will-own&quot; data-local-id=&quot;a651e14204b9&quot; data-renderer-start-pos=&quot;1341&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you will own&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li data-renderer-start-pos=&quot;1362&quot; data-local-id=&quot;208a901c5de0&quot;&gt;The Long Stays product vision, strategy and roadmap – across hybrid hospitality operators, student accommodation, aparthotels, coliving and adjacent segments – with direct accountability for ARR growth and product north star metrics.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-renderer-start-pos=&quot;1599&quot; data-local-id=&quot;1b12e186da2d&quot;&gt;The full resident lifecycle as a product capability: booking and lead-to-lease (monthly booking engine, tenant screening, contracting, guest verification and document collection); move-in and onboarding; billing and payments (recurring billing automation, &lt;span data-highlighted=&quot;true&quot; data-vc=&quot;highlighted-text&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;_kqswh2mm&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;_5pioz8co _189e1dm9 _1il9buyh _19lc184f _d0altlke&quot; data-testid=&quot;definition-highli

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Help make the world more hospitable &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The hospitality industry is uniquely human, and it deserves technology that’s just as inspiring as the people behind it. At Mews, we’re transforming the industry with a platform that helps hotels run smarter, move faster and create better guest experiences.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll work with smart, curious people who care deeply about what they do. You’ll have autonomy and the trust to make good decisions and move quickly. And you’ll enjoy a real sense of purpose as you see the impact of what we’re building.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you’re motivated by ownership, curiosity and meaningful impact, and are driven to deliver consistent high performance, you’ll feel at home here.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Let&#39;s get into the specifics. It’s impossible to capture every nuance of a role – especially at a rapidly growing company like Mews – but if we had to distil it into a job description (which we do because this is a job description), it would be this:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Director of Engineering&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re looking for a Director of Engineering to join our team and lead a critical part of our engineering organisation at a pivotal moment for Mews.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a senior leadership role for someone who can combine technical depth, organisational leadership, and strong product instincts. You’ll help shape the next chapter of our Front of House department, as we work toward a future where Mews recognises guests at scale, delivers personalised experiences across the journey, empowers staff with automation and next-best actions, and becomes the CRM of hospitality.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead and grow engineering teams through managers and senior individual contributors, creating clarity, accountability, and a high-performance culture.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with Product, Design, Data, and other engineering leaders to turn strategy into execution across a complex, cross-product area.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Set engineering direction that balances speed, quality, and long-term scalability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Raise the bar on engineering excellence, operational health, and delivery rigour in an environment where Front of House has made quality, proactive monitoring, and stronger governance a clear priority.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help teams ship the capabilities that matter most to our strategy, including areas such as guest recognition, personalised experiences, automation, role-aware workflows, and connected guest journeys.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive strong cross-tribe and cross-division collaboration, especially where ecosystem value depends on shared capabilities across Front of House, Back of House, Platform, and Fintech.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coach leaders to make sound decisions, reduce unnecessary complexity, and build teams that can move fast without collapsing under scale or operational pressure.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What Success Looks Like&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Success in this role means building an engineering organisation that can deliver against the core outcomes Front of House is aiming for:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Increasing the share of the guest journey powered by Mews&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Improving Guest Lifetime Value&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reducing Time to Serve for staff and guests&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It also means helping teams translate strategy into measurable outcomes, with clearer metrics, better prioritisation, and stronger links between engineering delivery and business impact.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What We’re Looking For&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Significant experience leading eng

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Help make the world more hospitable &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The hospitality industry is uniquely human, and it deserves technology that’s just as inspiring as the people behind it. At Mews, we’re transforming the industry with a platform that helps hotels run smarter, move faster and create better guest experiences.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll work with smart, curious people who care deeply about what they do. You’ll have autonomy and the trust to make good decisions and move quickly. And you’ll enjoy a real sense of purpose as you see the impact of what we’re building.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you’re motivated by ownership, curiosity and meaningful impact, and are driven to deliver consistent high performance, you’ll feel at home here.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Let&#39;s get into the specifics. It’s impossible to capture every nuance of a role – especially at a rapidly growing company like Mews – but if we had to distil it into a job description (which we do because this is a job description), it would be this:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p class=&quot;wnfdntt _1ibi0s3f5 _1ibi0s3ce _1ibi0s3ea&quot; data-pm-slice=&quot;1 1 []&quot;&gt;We’re looking for an experienced Employment Counsel to join our Legal team and partner closely with our People Team and senior business leaders. This is a high-impact role for someone who combines strong employment law depth with sound judgment, practical communication and the ability to bring clarity in a fast-moving, international environment.&lt;/p&gt;
